T|27 ·|0|The physical and runtime layer the whole Life OS runs on: three Mac minis, the Hermes gateway, OpenClaw ag setup, cron jobs and memories — all archived so the rebuilding ag had complete context.
T|27 ·|1|
T|Purp|0|Document the machines and runtime that host the ag. This isn't a single dashboard page so much as the infrastructure surfaced across the ag and Org Chart pages, plus the archived sy the new bd was based on.
T|Purp|1|
T|The |0|Mac Mini 2 — Hermes · Personal Layer, serves all workspaces. Runs the Hermes gateway (routing) and the personal C-suite ag: hy (Chief of Staff), Nexus (CTO), Steve (QA), Knox (sec), Wolf (fi).
T|The |1|Mac Mini 1 — OpenClaw · Workspace tier, produces the work. Runs the OpenClaw setup w/ the workspace/master ag that do production work.
T|The |2|Mac Mini 3 — Workshop & Services · Skill workshop, makes the team better. Dedicated to skill training/improvement (see 07-skill-workshop.md).
T|The |3|Mac Studio M5 (reserved) · future capacity — "Mac Studios coming."
T|The |4|
T|The |5|Fleet stats shown on the ag page: ~3 machines online, ~23 ag running, ~48 GB RAM in use, routing via Hermes.
T|The |6|
T|Conn|0|SSH / terminal direct connection to each machine, plus a screen-share option, so the owner can log in and fix things if the gateway goes down.
T|Conn|1|Hermes is the routing/gateway layer that directs work to ag/machines.
T|Conn|2|
X|The |0|A key part of the methodology (from the walkthrough):
X|The |1|The owner SSH'd into the Mac mini and made a complete cp of the existing OpenClaw setup — hy's main sy, all cron jobs, all memories, all workspaces from every ag, and the live codebase — and archived it into a reference folder.
X|The |2|Client reference builds were also placed in the reference folder (not shown publicly for privacy).
X|The |3|This gave the ag building the new project complete context and a complete knowledge base of what already exists, so they cld bd on top and make smarter, improvement-oriented choices rather than guessing.
X|The |4|
T|Why |0|The runtime is the substrate for everything else: ag live on these machines, rt through Hermes, run cron jobs, and read/write the sb-backed memory. Archiving the old sy in full is what made the redesign an improvement of something real rather than a greenfield guess.